===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Two possible interpretations:
* {{liushu|i}} – three small dots > small.
* {{liushu|p}} – three granules of sand – original character of {{och-l|沙}} > small.

Starting from some bronze inscriptions, the dots have become elongated. Based on this form, ''{{w|Shuowen}}'' erroneously considers it to be an {{Han compound|八|丨|ls=ic|nocap=1|t1=to divide; to separate|t2=small object}}.

Compare with {{och-l|少}}, represented by four dots in its oracle bone script form. Unrelated to the bottom part of [[京]], [[示]], [[尞]], [[尗]], and [[原]].

===Etymology 1===
Often thought to be related to {{och-l|少}} (e.g. {{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}), but {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} points out that the alternation between {{cog-lite|ltc|-}} {{IPAfont|/s-/}} and {{IPAfont|/ɕ-/}} within a word family is exceptional.

